# Vote.execute property

Execute Proposal

## Example

```javascript
// The proposal ID of the proposal you want to execute
const proposalId = "0";
await contract.execute(proposalId);
```

**Signature:**

```typescript
execute: {
        (proposalId: string): Promise<Omit<{
            receipt: ethers.providers.TransactionReceipt;
            data: () => Promise<unknown>;
        }, "data">>;
        prepare: (proposalId: string) => Promise<Transaction<Omit<{
            receipt: ethers.providers.TransactionReceipt;
            data: () => Promise<unknown>;
        }, "data">>>;
    };
```

## Remarks

Execute the related transactions for a proposal if the proposal succeeded.
